The paper is about conversational information seeking (CIS), which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the design of a modular architecture for CIS research, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, making cs.HC and cs.AI likely categories as well. Finally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning (DL) for CIS, which suggests cs.DL as a possible category.
